TERMINATION AND ALTERNATIVE SANCTIONS FOR ICF[SLASH]IID NONCOMPLIANCE (§9-4110)
    In order to qualify for Medicaid reimbursement, intermediate care facilities forersons with intellectual and developmental disabilities (ICFs/IID) shall complyith federal conditions of participation (CoPs), pursuant to 42 C.F.R. §§83.400-483.480.
      The CoPs include adherence to acceptable standards in theollowing areas:
    Governing body and management;
    Client protections;
    Facility staffing;
    Active treatment services;
    Client behavior and facility practices;
    Health care services;
    Physical environment; and
    Dietetic services.
    An ICF/IID that fails to maintain compliance with the CoPs may beubject to alternative sanctions and/or termination of its participation in theedicaid program.
